  "summary": "InLifeGram Pyrogram fork hides exec'd payload invoked with live bot session",
  "details": "InLifeGram is a republished fork of the Pyrogram MTProto client that adds two undocumented changes versus upstream. pyrogram/methods/utilities/app.py consists of a single statement that base85-decodes and zlib-decompresses an opaque ~11 KB blob and passes it to exec(), with an Indonesian comment self-labeling it as 'Encrypt Feature, Private Source'. pyrogram/methods/utilities/start.py imports that module under the alias 'secret' and, inside Client.start(), checks self.me.is_bot and calls secret.init(self) wrapped in try/except: pass, handing the live authenticated Client (including the bot token, MTProto session, and dispatcher) to the hidden payload. The hook only fires for bot accounts and is not mentioned in the README. Any developer who installs this fork and starts a bot silently grants the author arbitrary code execution with full control over the bot account (read/send messages, exfiltrate the token, join chats, persist).",
